description:
Begin at 3:15 AM on August 1st or any day after. Continue each day until August 31. The idea is to write in a hypnogogic/hypnopompic (between sleeps) state of altered consciousness.
    You may write any length, style, form, content, voice, rhythm, etc.
    DO NOT EDIT your work. This is raw stuff, baby. That's part of the experiment. You are welcome to edit, collage, break apart the poems later for whatever purpose you choose, but please SHARE THE RAW STUFF with the rest of the group here or on the website once the experiment is over.
    (Optional) Do not read what you have written until the month is over, except to skim the work to make sure everything is legible.

HOWEVER: if you'd like to come by Art Predator's camp to share, please do! 

September 1: Transcribe your scribbles. (Don't edit!!)
Submit raw work to the 3:15 website on your own page. See what others have written in 2013 or previous years.
print_description: It's the 20th anniversary of the 3:15 Experiment! Write at 3:15am any/all nights in August to join this altered states of consciousness writing ritual
title: 3:15 Experiment

description:
"Calling all of you facially hirsute throwbacks out there, gather 
up and deliver your fine self, along with your inner and outer 
beards to the House of the Automatic Subconscious, where we shall take the time to parade you before us like so much hairy meat and pass judgment upon those locks and curls that cascade off of the area known as your chinny-chin-chin. There will be 4 prime categories: Full-Beard, Moustache, Freestyle Full Beard, Fake Beard and quite probably not possibly, an 'Other' category.

As per usual in this sort of event, our highly esteemed panel of 
untrained professionals will judge upon such features as glossiness 
of pelt, lack of nits, creativity, fullness of body, amount of previous 
dinner ensconced within and other equally tangible parameters that attest to the care and feeding of your personal face troll. Bribery and foolishness are considered de rigueur.

All that is necessary is that you have some form of facial hair, a 
good and jolly spirit, and the necessary accoutrement of a cummerbund. One must have the proper air of formality around such an event as this, do not you agree?"

description:
Like to sing? Come to our vocal jam. Last year, we had a blast when a  
spontaneous chorus broke out in our camp, covering classic harmony-rich songs like Billy Joel's "For the Longest Time," and a tradition  
was born. We will gather and sing popular, well-known, or timeless  
songs in harmony (e.g., folk, pop, rock, opera, blues, barbershop, and  
on and on), without accompaniment (i.e., a capella). Song (lyric) sheets will be provided. All are welcome - no training needed.

description:
Look for our White Tower and tent and you'll find that We have what you need,
 some chilly snow in the desert!
	Every Afternoon Monday through Friday, from 1-3 you can come by our cool shade tent and chill out with a snow cone made just for you in the many flavors of Our choice. You may have any of the flavors we decide to give you, while the ice lasts.

	Over heated Kids may cut the line,(with Mom/Dad), and may ask for a Cone anytime in the day if they need it, providing we can find the ice for them.

	Need we say more?
No, But we can.
	We strive for the best and finest shaved ice snow to blend with the flavors and encapsulate them it a tasty cooling treat. We don't do Chunky snow!  There is a difference, and you'll know it as soon as your frozen treat melts gently on your Tongue releasing the sweet and/or sour bouquet to your waiting taste buds, refreshing you and cooling you while you enjoy the Art and other activities available in our camp. 
	Bring a new clean block of ice and you'll make friends for life and maybe get an extra treat too!
We do not do snow cups, or Bottles, because they are not a Snow Cone and there is a Difference!
print_description:
Try any flavor we decide for you.
Need we say more?
Mon-sat 1-3 in our cool shade tent.
Hot Kids may cut in or ask for one anytime if there's ice
title: Afternoon SnowCones at Contraptionists

description: ALIA can take a room into deep ecstasy with her bright energy and serpentine movements drawing from her training as a dance performer and her devotion to embodying the feminine, never playing anything that she herself won't move to. She has had a life-long love affair with music and dance - they are her spiritual practice and her most potent passions. ALIA transmits the bliss she experiences in performances to create a connected, alive and activated experience that evokes the sacred and awakens our connection to our source through rhythm and movement. She approaches every set as a ritual and as a facilitator of dance floor unity. ALIA has shared the stage with the likes of Beats Antique, Random Rab, Govinda, Freq Nasty, Marty Party, An-ten-nae, Heyoka, Pussymonster, Sasha Rose, Vibesquad, DJ Jocelyn, and Bay Area favorite DJ Dragonfly. On Soundcloud at www.soundcloud.com/aliarhythms On YouTube at www.youtube.com/aliarhythms On Twitter at www.twitter.com/alia_rhythms

description: As John Frum said, “Let there be ART!” this year consider finding out more about the fantastic art projects at Burning Man! This informal bike tour is hosted by volunteers from the ARTery (6:25 & Esplanade). A curated group of art projects will be visited and discussed. This tour will begin at 10:00 AM and run approximately 60-90 minutes. The tours are flexible so feel free to join us on playa if you see a bunch of bikes traveling in a pack, or drop out if you want. The tour starts promptly at the bike racks across from the ARTery (on the Esplanade). Note that there are also ART TOUR - Guided Tour (search Playa Events), and self guided tours (paper copies) available at the ARTery. Most of the art on the playa is self-funded, so be sure to check out your favorite art projects on the Burning Man website now, and then help fund them or volunteer through their respective websites. It takes every single one of us to make Burning Man happen...
print_description: ARTery curated bike tour of art projects.  Meet in front of ARTery. Whiteout permitting.
title: ART TOUR - Bicycles

description: It's all about the ART projects and the fabulous ARTISTS and their teams who create them! Ride in style on a bus/mutant vehicle as volunteers from the ARTery provide information on curated art pieces, as well as the Temple and The Man. Guided Vehicle tours run Tue-Fri and begin at 11:00 AM at Everywhere. Vehicle tours are meant for people with mobility issues -- seniors, pregnant women, people with ongoing or temporary disabilities, children, and others who might face challenges in getting out and around the playa. You must have tickets in advance to get a seat on the bus. Tickets are available @ noon THE DAY BEFORE a Everywhere (6:22 & Esplanade). description:
Yep, this really is what you think it is - a "mouth-on" workshop where we'll have a chance to ask questions, compare notes, share techniques, and generally learn from each other to be more skillful at this thing we love - or want to love - to do.  If you're interested in learning more about how to please your man orally, this is the place for you.

Come on ladies / givers, you know you've got some skills - and some questions!  Come share your favorite tips and techniques by words and demonstration, and ask questions that have been plaguing you.

	* Drool or dry? 
	* What about the gag reflex?
	* How do you use hands and still go deep?

And guys, you must have comments you'd like to pass on, other than simply "Yes, please"!

	* Hate teeth?  Want teeth?
	* What about deep throat?

Here's your chance to make your requests - and pet peeves - heard!

This is a participatory event open to couples of any combination, so long as one of them has some phallic protuberance and the other is applying lips, tongue, and maybe even throat to it.  No lookie-loos!
This was a great fun event at the last Burn.  The presenter's been researching all year to find new tidbits and info to share.  (Hey, someone's gotta do the tough jobs.)  Come show off, learn stuff, and have fun.
other_location: The Orgy Dome at camp "and then there's only LOVE"

description:
The mission of the Black Rock Arts Foundation is to support and promote community, interactive art and civic participation.

The Black Rock Arts Foundation (BRAF) was founded by several of the partners who founded and produce Burning Man, an annual arts festival in the Nevada desert. The Burning Man event, like no other environment in the world, has created a unique venue for art, and has rekindled one of art’s most valuable functions: connecting community members in creation, curiosity, and wonderment. At Burning Man, we observe how art brings people together, inspires participation and engenders meaningful connections between individuals. The art experienced at Burning Man invites individuals to interact with both the work itself and with their community at large.

BRAF was established to bring this modality of creating and coexisting with art to the rest of the world, with the vision that community-driven, inclusive, and interactive art is vital to a thriving culture. The foundation received its 501(c)3 status in November of 2001. Come learn more and see how  you can get involved.
print_description: The mission of the Black Rock Arts Foundation is to support and promote community, interactive art and civic participation.
title: Black Rock Arts Foundation

description:
10 reasons Burners and Mormons are a match made in heaven. 1) They both love temples, 2) settle in deserts, 3) build cities, and 4) are all about self sufficiency, 5) They love crazy ceremonies, 6) crazier visions, and 7) ornate pageants. 8) They both focus on the community, 9) spend liberally to support their cause, and 10) everyone agrees they're sooo nice. 

So let’s bring them together and see what happens. Mormons, former Mormons, and anyone intrigued by Mormonism are all welcome to come chat about Joseph Smith, Native American-Hebrew ancestry, your favorite broadway musical from the creators of South Park, or any other Mormon related topics. We'll be stocked with sparkling cider for the true believers, and champagne and beer for the rest.
print_description: Burners and Mormons are a match made in heaven: temples, deserts, city-building, visions. Come mingle and share a sparkling cider or ... beer.

description:
Black Rock Educators Consortium is an annual professional development opportunity that runs parallel to and in conjunction with the larger art festival in Black Rock City.

As educators, we all bring so much back to our classrooms from the playa. The goal of BREC is to create a staff development opportunity unlike any other- where we help each other to bring the magic home to our students. All educators are welcome; Early-childhood ed, K-12, higher ed, adult ed, certificated, classified, administrator or school board member, all are welcome! We all have something to share. 

Teach a breakout session! Collaborate on lesson plans! Bring home a slick flyer to share with your fellow educators!  Pick up a session listing and check out the break-out board! Can't make it to registration? Join us when you arrive.
print_description: A unique staff development opportunity for early childhood, K-12, and adult educators.   Bring home an impressive conference schedule for your admins!

description:
Join Black Rock Solar at its annual event Solar Playa International. While sipping on a mint julep or ice cold beer, you will get a chance to meet the staff and crew of Black Rock Solar as well as other Burners doing meaningful and innovative work around the country.  The purpose of this event is to bring together all of the different groups and individuals on playa doing work in renewable energy, climate change, environmental outreach, and policy.  Tell us about your projects and learn about ours. 

Since 2007 Black Rock Solar has been building solar arrays in Nevada and giving them away at little or no cost, over 3 megawatts of clean renewable energy to date.  Black Rock Solar prioritizes installations for schools, hospitals, rural communities, non-profit groups, and Native American tribes.
print_description: Have a cold mint julep, learn about our projects, tell us what you’re doing in the world of renewable energy, climate change & environmental outreach.

description: Mystery and Beauty are biological epi-phenomena that intertwine to produce intellectual and spiritual aesthetics. The mystery and beauty of what I have termed "psychedelic rationalism" will be discussed using the lens of gender. This is a new way of thinking about women's participation and contributions to psychedelic culture, and introduces the idea of a blended rationalist paradigm of psychedelic knowledge. Far from essentialist assumptions that men are from Mars and women are from Venus, this talk will discuss the sociology of male/female cooperation, knowledge, experience, and community-building in psychedelic circles. What emerges is a new paradigm for understanding inner-action/interaction.

hosted_by_camp.name: Soft Landing (formerly Camp Above the Limit)

print_description: Chelsea Starr discusses women's participation and contributions to psychedelic culture, and introduces the idea of a blended rationalist paradigm.
title: Blending the Mystery: Gender and Psychedelics

description:
The Body is Not an Apology is extending it's reach to Black Rock City in collaboration with Artisans Theatre Collective. This Body Acceptance Dance Party is a chance for all of us to let loose without feeling like we're being compared to the impossible commercial standards we face in the default world. Start the week off feeling fabulous about yourself with a playlist that includes Queen Latifah, Li'l Kim, Salt-N-Pepa, DJ Kool, Notorious BIG, A Tribe Called Quest and much more! Come and shake what your mama gave you and don't feel bad about it for one second. These are your people, you big beautiful burner!
There will be an art video/photo project being created, for posting on the internet after the event, which shows all of the variety of bodies we radically accept on the playa, not just the models that can make the director's cut for the "Places you'll go" video. Come and get your body painted as our artist sees fit and take a step to show off your radical self love!
There will be Sonoma County Sangria served at the Thirsty Camel bar and a multi-media dance extravaganza inside the dome. Special long distance appearance by performance poet and founder of TBINAA, Sonya Renee, via recorded audio and video.

description: OMG MUSIC WITH WORDS! Now in its eighth year on the playa, A Plus D bring BOOTIE BRC, the internationally-infamous mashup bootleg party, to Black Rock City! With guest DJs Lobsterdust, Entyme, Faroff, John!John!, Airsun, and more – along with mashup shows and performances throughout the night by  Alejandro and Adrian – Bootie BRC celebrates (and satirizes) pop culture both past and present, keeping your brain guessing and body dancing with creative song combinations. Mixing and matching every musical genre, era, and style into one big dance party, it's the soundtrack for the A.D.D. generation -- with free mashup CDs given away like candy! Launched in 2003 in San Francisco, Bootie was the first club night dedicated solely to the burgeoning artform of the bootleg mashup, and is now the biggest mashup event in the world, with regular parties in several cities on four continents. Bootie BRC is presented in part by the BRC Weekly, Black Rock City's independent newsweekly. Bootie ... because one song at a time just isn't enough.
print_description: OMG MUSIC WITH WORDS!! The greatest mashup party in the universe comes to BRC for its 8th year. DJs A Plus D and guests turn 2 songs into 1. Free CDs!

description: Love the art that you're experiencing on the playa? Wish you had art like this in your home town? Make it happen! Apply for a Black Rock Arts Foundation grant and create interactive art experiences in your community. The Black Rock Arts Foundation was founded in 2001, as a 501c3 non-profit, by several of the founding members of Burning Man. These founders wanted to fund like-minded, community-driven art experiences in the world. BRAF grants awards to about 10 grantees a year, ranging from $1000-$10,000 per project. BRAF's grants program has funded over 90 projects worldwide!Stop by the Everywhere Pavilion and talk to past grantees, members of the Grant Committee, and BRAF representatives who can answer all your questions about getting funding from BRAF. Get tips on proposal and budget writing. Come tell us about your great idea for an art project!

description: The Black Rock City Philharmonic Orchestra seeks musicians to bring a performance of Beethoven's 7th Symphony to the playa.  Crazy, you say?  Impossible?  No more unlikely than a deaf composer.  -- To create the Black Rock City Philharmonic (a five-year project), we need: 1) section leaders in San Francisco, New York, Western Canada, and Eastern Canada; 2) a bank of Burn-ready instruments; 3) a network of veteran burners who are also skilled musicians; and 4) a road map to guide us to our performance, three or four years down the road. Musicians, enthusiasts, roadies, visionaries, and realists are all welcome to talk about how to bring Beethoven to the playa.  Join us for the inaugural meeting of the Black Rock City Philharmonic, to be held at the Golden Cafe in the French Quarter.
print_description: Musicians sought to bring a performance of Beethoven's 7th to the playa in 2017. More info at the annual meeting of the BRC Philharmonic Orchestra.

description:
Brewing beer on the playa? Can't be done. No way; not with 60 degree temperature swings, only one week for fermentation, hippie-quality sanitation, and pyromaniacs  stealing your flamethrowers when you're trying to boil the wort. We're going to do it anyways. On a camp stove, with a pot that's too small. By the end of the class, you'll have gone through the process; you'll know how to brew beer! Will you remember by the time you get home? Fat chance.

Barring disaster, it'll be fermented, carbonated, and kegged by the end of the week. Drinkable? We'll see.

21+ only

description:
It ain't like the spankings you got as a kid. This has RHYTHM! For those who do want a bit more zing in their play, come join us for a hands-on workshop. Come explore the experience of percussion being a source of erotic heat and arousal!
We'll talk about techniques and timing and psychology, about rhythm and drum sets - all with hands-on demonstrations and encouragement to explore on your own.  Where's the sweet spot?  How do you warm up?  Why bother to warm up?  How do you "read" the “drum”?
On the other side, how do you relax into being drummed?  Why would you want to?
Is it pain?  Is it pleasure?  Is it excitement? Is it music? Is there a difference?  Bring your own partner, or find one at the workshop, for a romp into this paradoxical, rhythmic world.
other_location: The Orgy Dome at camp "and then there's only LOVE"

description:
Was John Frum a racist? Is the current theme of BM ignoring the dangers of colonialism, power, and privilege? 
Explore the ways race, class, gender, power, and privilege affect your experience on and off playa.

This workshop is a challenge to the theme that Cargo Cult is all about aliens, visitors returning, and celebrating John Frum. Come join in an interactive workshop that will explore the shadow side of John Frum including the negative impact of colonialism, the glorification of material objects, the destruction of native lands and culture, America's lack of responsibility for military endeavors, and the current impact of this Cargo Cult story. This workshop will explore our shared reality of how racism, classism, and sexism affect our current Burning Man community. We welcome people of all backgrounds to this workshop and to this exploration of how the oppression we were taught in every day society plays out on playa. We will explore the difficulties of the current paradigm and how that affects our ability to form a new experimental community. There will be space to address how we as the BM community want to create change on and off playa.
print_description: Was John Frum a racist? Is Cargo Cult about colonialism, power, and privilege? Explore how race, class, gender,& privilege affect your BM experience.
title: Cargo Cult or Celebration of Colonialism?

description: sure a bloody mary at 8 might wake you up, but that shit be temporary.  wake up for good, and for always.  see into the source of all things, and realize that you are it, always were, ain't no effort to flow in the river of the present moment, and let it dance you. C.E.C. - Black Rock offers 15 minutes instruction on a basic mindfulness technique, shinzen young style,  followed by a 40 minute guided meditation.  meditate, celebrate, elevate: these are the trinity of the CEC.  the meditation gets you clear, the celebrate gets you fire, and the elevate brings you up where there's no coming down.    bring a yoga mat 30 minutes early for a pre-sit stretch.  bring your own cushion.  bring your own illusion, and watch it fall like gauze. until all loving things are saved from stifling, faithfully yours, secretary of secretaries.

description: The Celestial Fusion Communicator will be erected in front of our lounge, ready to call out to the Heavenly Ones for more inter-galactic gifts.  As an assemblage of gongs, drums, bells and chimes cobbled together from recycled instruments and modern found objects, the Communicator will be available to all comers for their radical musical self-expression.  Demandingly loud or sweetly plaintive, rhythms and unique sonic punctuations will fly to the cosmos as prayers and petitions, reinforced at night with beams of light.  The Communicator will invite impromptu solo performances as well as many-handed jam sessions, and will be a focal point of our camp's Thursday afternoon party.  (We'll take away the drumsticks late at night.)

description:
YOU ALWAYS WANTED TO RUN OFF AND JOIN THE CIRCUS...

NOW YOU CAN!

Come earn your clown nose at Circus Boot Camp. You've seen feats of skill on the Playa, and who hasn't dreamed of running off to join the Circus. Heck, half of y'all probably still dream in acrobats and clowns.  At Circus Boot Camp, we'll teach you to juggle, unicycle, hoop, slack line, trapeze, crack a whip and indulge your childish fancy in other circus-inspired arts.

I know what you're thinking: "Sure, you'll teach me to juggle... after I've spent years on the road washing elephants and dodging monkey poop!" Wrong! Our goal is nothing less than to bring the joys of object manipulation, unicycling and other circus arts to the Playa masses in a casual, friendly and fully clothed environment (ok, mostly-clothed).

Already a circus pro? Come test your mettle on our slackline; dance your clown shoes through the obstacles of irony; pass clubs with seasoned semi-professionals; try your hand at the Valley of One-Wheeled Doom!!
print_description: Juggle balls/clubs/fire; unicycle; crack whips; slackline; aerial silks/rope; hooping; cyr wheel & more!  Beginners and experts welcome!

description: CODAME on The Playa is an Art+Tech celebration that reaches out to the creative developer community on The Playa. Our mission is to bring together artists, technologists, and designers that push the boundaries of hardware, software, and physical/digital mediums for one evening to play and share. Our ultimate goal is to leave our participants and audience with one of the most unique Art+Tech experiences. In the end we would love to see a seed of inspiration taking bloom in someone’s eyes and diffusing creative digital glow through their entire spirit. If you think you've got that special sparkle in you to inspire others, looking for the ways to get  inspired, or just want to play and hang around with like-minded people, join us on Tuesday, the 29th, after dusk at our camp Clusterf*uck United for the dimension of " code" me on The Playa experience.

description: Contradancing all levels every night to live music - looped/ traditional/ celtic/ fusion/ techno; fast-paced yet easy to learn with a caller who instructs (but with room for dancers to improvise). Half the moves are with your partner, half with everyone else - so it has a tribal vibe, where the Zen is flow, synchrony, and bonding (not footwork, not competition). The repeated cycles of movement give dancers a long time to catch on.  In any case if you are smiling you are doing it right.  Dancers adjust their behavior to each new dancer they come to and gently realign fellow dancers if needed making contradancing one of the most accessible group dance forms, with for example mentally disabled, blind, deaf and wheelchair bound dancers at many dances.  Friendly to children and adults carrying children.  Sunset - midnightish (later if everyone keeps going), except Sat starts 30 min after the man falls, Sun starts 60 min after the temple burn begins.  Go to website to 'taste' dancing (including headcam video) and music.
print_description: Contradancing all levels every night to live music -  fast-paced yet easy to learn with a caller who instructs (with room for dancers to improvise).

description: Invented in the late 1800's, the cloud chamber is a small aquarium sized tool used for observing the trails left behind as charged particles from the cosmos shower on to the earth. This is the device that sparked the fire of modern experimental particle physics by allowing the pioneers of the science to provide evidence for the existence of particles that resulted from nuclear decay processes. The particles from the cosmos above shower the playa every second of every day and now you too can see them with your naked eye. Bring your cameras and try and snag a shot to take back with you!
print_description: Protons, electrons and muons, oh my! Particles from the cosmos above shower the playa every second and now you too can see them with your naked eye.

description:
Calling all students, staff, faculty, alumni, and friends of California Institute of Integral Studies! As classes begin back home in San Francisco, we know there are many of us right here in Black Rock City. Instead of meeting in the halls to talk about how "great the burn was this year," and how “we should meet up next year,” let's get together on the Playa to celebrate our amazing community and the unique institution that we call home. PCC Professor Richard Tarnas will give an enlightening talk on the historical role of “heroic communities” in transforming the world (like CIIS and Burning Man). Wear your best Playa fashions, bring your friends and family, and maybe even get some ideas for your next academic paper. Let’s elevate “school spirit” to a new dimension while we enjoy each other outside of our default roles. We’ll have some drinks, we’ll have some laughs, and we’ll dance with reckless abandon as we get ready to transform the (default) world.

COSMOCPOIA [address]
Tuesday, August 27, 8PM
print_description: Gather with students, faculty, staff, alumni & friends of the California Institute of Integral Studies to share stories, ideas, & cocktails.
title: Cosmocopia CIIS Community Mixer w/ Richard Tarnas

description:
Shonagh Home, author of 'Love and Spirit Medicine,' will discuss her encounters with a group of intelligences that have presented themselves to her through her shamanic work with the sacred mushroom.
 
Bio:
Author, shaman and spell breaker, Shonagh Home takes her students beyond the cultural mass-trance and into the territory of the sacred. She works with both individuals and groups to foster new paradigms and awaken self-healing. Through her writing, she shares mystery teachings about the magic of the body, the reclaiming of ourselves as True Human Beings, and our ability to engage with the technology of nature. She teaches workshops that are deeply transformative, helping people to release from old behavior patterns and access a wealth of inner resources. description:
So you need a thing…
A primer on digital fabrication.  i.e. Getting stuff made with digital tools.
This is a short lecture and longer discussion group on making things with:  CNC routers and mills, Laser cutters/engravers.  Also touching on water jet, plasma tables, and 3D printers.  
Facilitated by Shoeshine, an instructor at San Diego’s premier group shop – Makerplace.
Topics include:  Design software and file formats, 2D vs. 2.5D vs. true 3D,  materials, design and strategy  for digital production,  different processes  -  pros and cons of each, ways of learning the tools, finding access, online and 3rd party resources, bridging the gap between art and manufacturing, and whatever else the collective mind wants to delve into.
Note:  This is aimed at folk who would like to make use of these incredible technologies but don’t know where to begin.  Though experienced users/makers are welcomed and encouraged to come and add to the discussion.
Loads of examples to view, handle, and talk about … Q&A session to follow… and schwag!!!
print_description: Primer: CNC, lasers, 3D, others. Software, finding access. Where to begin? This is for you. Veteran makers welcome. Lots of examples
title: DIY Digital Fabrication

description:
Welcome Bakers, Builders and Hi Gluten Fans!

In the Black Rock City tradition of emergency and experimental shelter, the world’s first building made of 805 bread loaf bricks is being constructed at the Skinny Kitty Tea Lounge camp. ( please fill in location as we have not been assigned a space yet)

We finally found a solid use for white bread; it’s the perfect building block. If you’ve ever wondered about the compressive strength of a 10 day old loaf, make a point to come by and marvel at this free-standing enclosed structure. The material for this abode can be grown in one growing season and has an insulation value of R-5. The inspiration for this 10 foot diameter Dome of Dough is the traditional beehive shape of the charcoal kilns in Death Valley.

Crawl inside, wonder at the meditative vibe and who knows, maybe there will be fresh bread and jam for snacking.

WARNING: HI Gluten Zone!

Submitted by Howie Hawkes, AKA Hawkster, howie@hawkesconstruction.com
print_description: In the BRC tradition of emergency/experimental shelter visit the world’s first building made of bread loaves. Stop by Skinny Kitty Tea Lounge camp.
title: Dome of Dough

description:
Awaken your life force using simple techniques that integrate tapping, moving, and breathing. Wisdom in the language of movement. Neolithic shamanism.   All are welcome, especially beginners.
•	Come join us for a light heart-ed exploration of Qigong, an ancient book of wisdom written in the language of movement.  You'll discover that you have all the resources you need to keep your body healthy and your mind at peace, using these simple, yet profound movements.  Jump, tap, shake, sway, and breath yourself into a state of tranquility & health.  There will be an emphasis on practical application; this is a workshop and ritual, not a lecture! All are welcome, especially beginners.  Open yourself to the magic coursing within. Qigong is much gentler than most forms of yoga, and a wonderful complement to a vigorous yoga practice. Both practices have a common source, Neolithic shamanism.
print_description: Awaken your life force using simple techniques that integrate tapping, moving, and breathing. Wisdom in the language of movement. Neolithic shamanism.
title: Dragon Gate Qigong

description:
The soulful conviction of Eric Hayes floods his audience with a hearty stew of rich tones and silky vibes. Even those whose thirst is never quenched cannot help but set down their drink, close their eyes and give in to the seductive musings of this rising star. Hailing from New Jersey, Eric Hayes is so much more than your all-American musician. His music possesses a stirring, earthy sound that leaves his fans aching for more. His voice is robust. His talent is pure. His passion is unmatched.

The 31 year old Far Hills native and William Paterson University music graduate has been the recipient of several positive reviews by prestigious critics and has been featured in the Star Ledger, New York Village Voice Magazine, New York Post, the ASPCA and a host of online blogs and pop culture media sites.

Hayes' credits include collaborating and performing with several big name artists such as Gavin Degraw, Martin Sexton, Bill Withers, Rusted Root, Indie artist Rachel Platten, Reggae legend Ziggy Marley and soul artist Joss Stone.

2013 has been and continues to be an incredible year for Hayes. He is truly humbled by the invitation to perform and share his music at Burning Man 2013 on the night the "Man Burns" for Black Rock City and such an incredible community of artists.

Hayes is well known for his musical charity work and has headlined exclusive events held by some of the world’s most elite circles of hosts including the opening dinner ceremony for the United States Olympic Wrestling Team and headlining the internationally recognized American Giving Awards winning "More Than Me" charity. 
He is inspired by both male and female artists including Otis Redding, Sam Cooke, Miles Davis, Jimi Hendrix, Susan Tedeschi and Radio Head. Recently Hayes performed at the annual ASPCA fund raising charity event, attracting more than 15,000 people, during which he reportedly helped friend and animal advocate Prince Lorenzo Borghese raise more than $50,000 for animal welfare.
print_description:
Passionate. Powerful. Blue Eyed Soul.
The robust vocal conviction of NJ's Eric Hayes floods his audiences with rich tones and stirring, earthy vibes.
title: Eric Hayes Live at Burning Man 2013

description: Exploring empathy as the capacity to lead us from an ecological dark age and inform the applications of genetics and bioremedation into society. This talk is an invigorating and inspiring synthesis of scientific discoveries, shamanic techniques, communications with animal, plant, planetary intelligence and transcending the "Other" with empathy as primary toolkit for understanding the biology and consciousness of different sentient organisms. Tapping into the ability of shamans to imagine themselves imbuing the traits of animals has been a valuable way for a consciousness to expand itself beyond its biological parameters as we reach the apex of the ecological collapse, and realize the potential to unlock new horizons of what it means to be human in a post human identity culture.

description: I used to have a negative voice in my head criticizing my every choice, and I was unhappy.  Learn how I changed my thinking by taking new actions and connecting with my higher spirit. Class will include instructor’s story and lessons learned followed by group sharing and then a 20 minute meditation to start your shift in thinking.

description: You don't have to be on steroids to be able to hit a "homerun" in FIZZBALL!  All you really need to be able to do is to be able to beat the living shit out of a full can of really cheap beer giving the adoring crowds your best Barry Bonds imitation.  A case of crappy warm beer, soft underhanded tosses, and drunken half-naked (or fully naked!) people make for our own unique spinoff of our national pastime.  You drink what you hit and if you don't want warm suds cascading down on your sparkly playa finest, feel free to strip naked when it's your turn to be Casey At The Bat.  FIZZBALL at Barbie Death Camp.  A splendid time is guaranteed for all.  And remember:  Safety third.

description: Learn more about your fellow burners in this lively, interactive game. Players assemble as a group and field questions related to “Cargo Cult,” materialism, worship, and other topics. Rather than speaking, each player indicates their answer by moving to one side of the space or the other. See for yourself who agrees with you and who doesn’t. It’s a discussion in which everyone participates all the time (not just the loudmouths). Come with friends to share this bonding experience, or come on your own and make new friends at Camp Baggage Check!

description: For women. Become all that you are. Become all that you wish to be. Become all that you dare to be. What can you discover about yourself? What would you like to heal, explore, celebrate? For more info join the Basic Bodywork and Ecstatic Touch workshop David leads early each afternoon in the HeebeeGeebee chill space, or in the classroom, see schedule for Joyful Practical Tantra class. Ask for a mini-process orientation following the workshop, or make an appointment at the HBGB reception table. description: "Creative thinking is the process of generating new and useful ideas in any domain e.g., in the arts, in business, at home, in science etc. It is a cognitive skill which involves stimulating the brain to make new associations and connections in order to create an original thought – this is how creative ideas are made!Creativity is the ability to see what everyone else sees, but see and think what nobody else is seeing or thinking!Our Creative Thinking training course is designed to teach you the processes of creative thinking using a tool-kit of practical creativity techniques. It is a highly practical course which focuses on teaching you how to be more creative in your everyday environment. This means that you will be able to brainstorm new ideas on demand whether you are working on your own or in groups."

description: Black Rock City's LGBTQQ community kicks off the week in festive rainbow colors with libations, music and an exchange of info on the week's gay-oriented events. This premier annual opening-night gathering for the Playa's Gay/Bi/Curious Burners and their friends is hosted by Down Low Club Camp in memory of Mario Cisneros, founder of the event. Come meet new friends, reaquaint with those from past Burns, perhaps spark a new Playa romance or rekindle one from the past. Gather with your LGBTQQ brothers and sisters to learn where they are camped and what events they've got planned for the week on the Playa. Don't forget to bring a flyer or other info about your gay-oriented events to post on our LGBT Community Bulletin Board.

description:
Holotropic Breathwork™ is a powerful approach to self-exploration and healing that integrates insights from modern consciousness research, anthropology, various depth psychologies, transpersonal psychology,
Eastern spiritual practices, and mystical traditions of the world. The
name Holotropic means literally "moving toward wholeness" (from the
Greek "holos"=whole and "trepein"=moving in the direction of something).

The process itself uses very simple means: it combines accelerated
breathing with evocative music in a special set and setting. With the
eyes closed and lying on a mat, each person uses their own breath and
the music in the room to enter a non-ordinary state of consciousness.
This state activates the natural inner healing process of the
individual's psyche, bringing him or her a particular set of internal experiences. With the inner healing intelligence guiding the process,
the quality and content brought forth is unique to each person and for
that particular time and place. While recurring themes are common, no
two sessions are ever alike.

hosted_by_camp.name: Soft Landing (formerly Camp Above the Limit)

print_description: Holotropic Breathwork is an approach to self-exploration and healing that integrates insights from psychology and a variety of mystic traditons.
title: Holotropic Breathwork Workshop with Sheelo Bohm

description:
Young food activists are sparking a renaissance of a 150 year old order - The Grange.  A national organization having its roots in family farms and community halls. 

Many Granges have become home to food literacy and sovereignty activists and the slow foods movement.

While the Grange has its roots in a fraternal organization from the start it supported woman having an equal voice and vote.

The California State Grange is a leader in the Grange revitalization and was an early advocate of GMO labeling. 

California Prop 37 was initiated by a Granger.  California is one of many Granges throughout the country that are supporting a return of agriculture to local farming, organics, sustainable practices, alternative energy and localization of living and working.  We actively support the arts, music, education, youth and engage in a variety of community service projects.

California Grange is on the forefront of revitalizing this organization that was founded after the Civil War by family farmers who opposed domination by big banks and railroads that controlled markets and prices. 

Corporatocracy is ever more powerful and many Granges actively oppose it.

Come learn about the Grange and how we work to create relevant communities whether urban or rural rooted in family and friendship.
print_description: Discover the Grange a grass root org started by populist farm radicals who fought big banks & railroads. We grow relevant & resilient communities.
title: Home on the Grange

description:
Did you ever wonder why you feel a nagging emptiness, even though you meditate every day? Think you may be missing something, or maybe .. hitting something that isn't there? Wonder why everything is harder now that you've started to meditate?

You're probably NOT meditating! Or at least, you're not being told what is NOT meditation! For centuries, techniques that have been used successfully on eastern type folks seem to be falling flat in The West, and there are some questions you may not have asked, or had answered. Join Zyg, a veteran of Not Meditating, for a talk and workshop on How Not to Meditate. Mediation cannot be discussed, but only experienced.. Zyg hopes to steer you into an authentic understanding of Meditation, and of sitting, standing, or whatever else you may be doing that is not meditation. Especially Meditation.
print_description: Can you feel there is a more authentic experience that lies beyond Meditation? Join Zyg for a workshop on How Not To Meditate!

description:
This is a presentation that narrates a personal healing process through the use of entheogenic agents. These agents provided the transcendent space that allowed inner wounds to be reconfigured into a more manageable and workable form, releasing the soul from inner/outer conflict.

Experiences with three different entheogenic agents enabled me to access states of consciousness that fostered healing in my familial relationships by re-framing conflicts, through form of visions and wider understandings, in pictorial, mythological, and transcendent narratives. These experiences in the Other Worlds have been translated into substantial and concrete shifts in the Ordinary World.

This journey through the ‘immaterial' considers entheogenic agents as psychological/emotional catalysts for transformation and growth. The Jungian framework of alchemy and individuation has been central in filtering my transformational process and the focus is on its relevance to integrating psychedelic explorations.
print_description: This presentation narrates a personal healing process through the use of entheogenic agents.
title: In Search of the Philosopher's Stone

Sacred Dance
Blossoming through all lies sacredness, the true feminine principle of quiet thunder. Experience the movements & awaken the power within.
Blossoming through all yet imperceptible to many lies sacredness, the true feminine principle of quiet thunder.  Long forgotten but recently rediscovered behind a fake wall in the White Cloud Monastery in China, 24 drawings of the Jade Maiden guide us back to the feminine practice of Qigong and our feminine essence.  Each one of us must balance and unite the male & female powers within, and  restore balance to the world. Come experience the movements of this Sacred Dance, deciphered from these drawings,  & awaken the feminine power within using this ancient wisdom.  All are welcome.

description:
Presenting the Culmination of
a Dazzling Romance Unlike Any Other

Jenjen Wong & Noah Zilberberg
Friday, August 30, 2013
6pm @ The Trash Fence
Burning Man Festival
Black Rock City, Nevada

Join us to witness and celebrate our union at 6pm "The Golden Hour” of the day at the legendary “Trash Fence” about 100yds to the right of Point 3 (straight out from the man/temple line and a little to the right).

Come by foot, bike or art car! Those seeking a ride via Love Potion/Amphora Art Car have the option of meeting at Camp Manifestation (9:35&E) at 5:00pm-5:15pm.

You are invited to wear your playa best and join us for a champagne toast after the ceremony.

A Side Note: If you have never been to the trash fence you may think we are crazy to have such a special ceremony at such a strange place. Well we are crazy but you will soon understand why the trash fence sounds like rubbish to some and magic to others…

Why Burning Man? Crazy right!?
Why yes we are! And since BM is where we met, it seemed the most perfect place for us to get married. There is NO obligation to attend. If you can join us, we'd love to have you! We are so happy to have a wedding without seating arrangements so the MORE the MERRIER!
print_description:
Presenting the Culmination of
a Dazzling Romance Unlike Any Other

Jenjen & Noah
Fri, Aug 30, 2013
6pm @The Trash Fence
100yds to right of pt 3
title: Jenjen & Noah's Wedding - Fri, Aug 30 - 6pm

The 2009 version of this event won the Acculturation Video award from Burning Man (http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dtX8Z-izffs\). description: Kama Flight Massage blends the dynamism of contact improv, the serene flow of Watsu, the deep release of Thai massage and the exhilaration of aerial yoga.  It comprises a new somatic modality for reanimating the body with its improvisatory flow and playful exploratory freedom. Supported on a massage table with your body borne aloft on the continually moving fulcrum of the practitioner’s body, the receiver is moved through a wide range of extended postures.  Using a suite of practiced movements, such as pivoting his body under different joints of your body, the giver is able to move the receiver seamlessly and weightlessly throughout the course a session. He safely levers the receiver’s body into increasingly extended and pleasurable positions that combine deep hip opening, pivoting and spinal decompression that, collectively, evoke a deep state of surrender.
print_description: It blends the dynamism of contact improv, the serene flow of Watsu, the deep release of Thai massage & the exhilaration of aerial yoga.

description:
Standing on a 8’ tall altar, the 6-armed idol reaches 30' into the air to spew fireballs from flame-cannons mounted at the end of each arm, beseeching the Deep-Voiced Spirits in the Sky to bring cosmic cargo to the dusty city.
As the desert burners gather at the feet of the idol, they cogitate into a prayer-trance, beaming waves of mental energy, focusing and preparing for the bearers of cosmic cargo. Using brainwave-oracles to channel mental energy, the supplicants invoke the Tesla-Jinn and energize the cargo ritual, producing a fiery prayer-ring-of-hands, circling overhead faster and faster, and as the coil begins to energize a hoary crown of high voltage discharge develops a dome of plasma, arcing and sparking wildly, as the electromagnetic prayer is transmitted out into the heavens, and as the transubstantiation is at zenith the distant sound of approaching Voices can be heard, building in volume as a host of heavily-laden, ground-shaking, cargo-bearing bird machines bears down on the encampment, growing louder and louder until the thunderous, throbbing drone of a chorus of engines shakes the tower and brings an eruption of devotional energy as precious cosmic cargo rains down upon the blessed worshipers of dust and fire. Weather permitting.

We invite you to strap on a brainwave "oracle" and watch the monitor as you control your brainwaves and fire the flame cannons, invoking the "Cosic Cargo Routine".

Brain cleansing services may be available throughout the day but we cannot commit to being properly staffed except on the posted time and date. We expect to be operational each night around dusk at the Hookah Lounge, providing at least one of the operating crew still survives and is able to awake the Jinn.

description:
Start your evenings (5PM: M, Tu, W, F) or days (10AM: Th, Sa) with the most intense laughter you can experience.  
We laugh for no reason, other than for exercise, and health. Relieve  
stress and pain, promote natural healing, and create spontaneous bonds  
of friendship through group laughter. It’s fun! The brainchild of Dr.  
Madan Kataria in India and practiced by millions worldwide, Laughter  
Yoga combines Unconditional Laughter with Yogic Breathing (Pranayama).  
Anyone can Laugh for No Reason, without relying on humor, jokes or  
comedy. Laughter is simulated as a body exercise in a group; with eye  
contact and childlike playfulness, it soon turns into real and  
contagious laughter. The concept of Laughter Yoga is based on a  
scientific fact that the body cannot differentiate between fake and  
real laughter. One gets the same physiological and psychological  
benefits. Find much more info online by searching on Laughter Yoga,  
but come! Enjoy!
print_description: Laughter as exercise! Laugh with others in childlike playfulness and experience all the health benefits of a good, long laugh!
title: Laughter Yoga

description:
Are you ready to change your life?  

Find love?
Fix a relationship?
Tell the truth?
Lose weight?
Create a new career?
Dismantle your excuses?
Be happy?
Take down your dark side?
Start dreaming again?
Stop limiting what's possible for yourself?
And LOVE your whole LIFE?

Guess what is standing in your way? YOU! 
And we're here to fix that. Like a chiropractor who adjusts your body, we adjust your life emotionally, mentally and spiritually, helping you see what's holding you back and giving you the tools to create the life you want.

Camp IMAGINEnation is a life coaching camp dedicated to the power of dreaming and radical honesty. Our Life Coaches are trained in The Handel Method and go through an extensive 2-year or more training process on life issues and human behavior. 

Camp IMAGINEnation was founded by The Handel Group and born of an authentic and ambitious desire to change the world in a very positive way. It is a spiritual endeavor for us. We think that those who are willing to dig deep and look at themselves honestly are the most courageous people in the world, not to mention, people we’d want to hang with. In a word, we are looking to make personal development cool. We think it is. 

The Handel Method was developed over the last 15 years by HG Co-founder and Chairman, Lauren Zander. The method is the foundation for not only our life coaching work, but also for the courses we teach at MIT, NYU, Rutgers and Stanford Business Schools, and for the work we do within large companies in the Executive Coaching Division. The method is revolutionary yet easy to understand, methodical yet infinitely customizable. Most importantly of all, it has proven to be highly effective.

Together we dig deep, play big and don’t stop until goals are fulfilled and lessons learned. We care, we love what we do and we walk our talk.
print_description:
Life Coaching 
False Idol & 6:30
Mon-Sat 12-4
A life coaching camp dedicated to the power of dreaming and radical honesty.
title: Life Coaching

description:
What is the meaning of life in 5 words? If you’re lucky enough to find the Tree of Life reaching for the sky, you realize you had the answer all along.  
The "Life in 5 Words" project began in the desert of Black Rock City, at Burning Man 2010. 
A small wooden desk is built on the side of the road. It is guarded by the Tree of Life, a "palm" tree with leafy hands outstretched to the sky.  Inside there is the blank Book of Life. Anyone who opens this mysterious book is greeted with the question “What is the meaning of life?” The Catch: your answer has to be in 5 words, no more no less. 
Answers will be written within the book’s dusty pages throughout the week of Burning Man. Ravers, demons, and dusty pilgrims will stop to reflect and contribute their answers. It is a shared experience; anyone and everyone has access to the book.
print_description: What is the meaning of life in 5 words? If you’re lucky enough to find the Tree of Life reaching for the sky, you realize you had the answer all along
title: Life in 5 Words

description:
The sun’s just up, but not too hot yet, but clothing is optional here,  so adults only, please. Come for an early hour of low impact exercise  in the Longevity Stick Art (LSA) discipline of 12 low-impact exercises  
to build balance, flexibility, strength, mental focus, breathing capacity, and vitality, and open your points and channels. Bring your water or hydration liquid. We’ll have sticks available for you. Master Mai Bac Dao developed the Longevity Stick Art discipline while he was a prisoner of war of the North Vietnamese Army. He helped his fellow  prisoners restore and maintain their health through LSA, and vowed that if he was ever freed, he would dedicate his life to spreading its benefits to the world, with the proviso that no future trainer could ever charge for the course. (Sounds like "gifting," eh?) He was freed, settled in Southern California, and started teaching classes of students and future teachers. Today, there are dozens of classes weekly around So Cal. Also, LSA is spreading around the US and world.  
Many more details are available at:  HYPERLINK 
"http://www.longevitystick.org/Longevitystick.org/Home.html " www.longevitystick.org/Longevitystick.org/Home.html and  HYPERLINK "http://www.filmbaby.com/films/2341 "  
Master Dao passed away late 2010 at age 89, and I was privileged to attend his funeral, and his last birthday party, a few months before.
print_description: Sun’s up, but not too hot. Clothes optional. Lo impact exercise for balance and open points & channels. Bring H2O. We got sticks for you. Adults only.
title: Longevity Stick Art

description:
Connecting Through Your Roots. Through breathing, cleansing and guided meditation, establish your divine connection with Mother Earth. Gravity central.Grounding is a vital component of daily balanced living. It allows us to deepen our connection with mother earth, or Gaia, and source energy. It teaches us how to release stress, stay focused, clear the chatter from our minds and auric fields, and eliminate free radicals from our bodies. When we connect with Gaia, we begin to realize that we are all safe and well provided for. We learn to understand our greater truths and to let go of fear, anger, guilt and anxiety. This allows us to establish a connection with our divine authentic self.

Whether you are a seasoned meditator or novice, you are invited to experience an ancient Eastern meditation breathing technique that has been passed on from master to master for centuries to achieve self-enlightenment. In this workshop you will learn about the chakra system, with an emphasis on the root, sacral and solar plexus. Our chakras govern our life force energy as well as our glandular, mental and emotional systems. Through the use of sage, crystals and sound we will also start to understand basic cleansing of our auric field and our surroundings. We will utulize ancient grounding techniques and a guided meditation to establish our connection with Gaia, help transform our outlook, and feel more grounded in our everyday lives.
print_description: Connect Through Your Roots. Through breathing, cleansing and guided meditation, establish your divine connection with Mother Earth. Gravity central.
title: Me and Mother Earth

description: Medicine Dance is a somatic, ecstatic and shamanic dance ceremony supporting the emergence of living Oneness and what it truly means to be embodied and aware in all of our Humanness. It is fun & empowering. Anyone can do it. Using movement, we work with the 5 elements of Earth, Water, Fire, Air and Ether to access the unique Medicine that is encoded within each of us and create a deeper relationship to our Selves, Others, and LIFE. By having an experiential understanding of how these elements work, we gain tools that help us to move through life in a more centered & conscious manner, embracing the shifting currents as exactly the Medicine we need for our healing & growth. We come together peacefully to create a deep space of exploration, safety, shared practice, transformation and community.

description: Our goal for this "Miso soup camp" is to prevent electrolyte imbalance for Burners. According to wikipedia, Pure miso paste nutritional information: Although high in sodium (over 400% DV), one cup (275 g) of miso paste is an excellent source of dietary fiber (59%) and protein (64% DV), as well as a good source of minerals . Miso paste is also high in amino acids, the basic building blocks of protein. An excellent source of vitamin K and a decent source of riboflavin (38% DV), miso also provides small amounts of other vitamins. One major benefit of miso is its extremely high omega-3 and omega-6 fatty acid content. We believe Miso saves Burners life on the Playa and leave them with good health all day.
print_description:
We serve Miso Soup in the morning.
Stimulate yourself with Miso Soup after "Hard Night" on the Playa.
(Please bring your own cup and spoon)
title: Miso Soup

description:
Walk the line between science and shamanism with volcanologist and spiritual seeker Allison Austin, whose groundbreaking new research proves that our planet has a consciousness and is speaking to us through volcanoes. 

There is an ancient code about the energetic nature of the Earth preserved in volcano mythology, which defines a global grid of sacred geometry whose symbolism reflects the legends themselves. These new maps of our planet connect pyramids, stone circles, mysterious sites, powerful cities, and geologic wonders around the world, giving us a deeper understanding of the forces that control our geography, politics, culture, collective consciousness, and even our cosmic lifelines. 

Explore a vision of a living planet once shared by our ancestors, long forgotten in our masculine-dominated, linear-thought world. Our Earth is alive! What she has to say will change you forever...

description:
(Nothing but) Flowers

You've travelled to the ends of the Earth, cast aside your default life, and willingly peered over the Edge. Now what?

(Nothing but) Flowers is a seminar devoted to the propagation of Burning Man core principles in the default world. In keeping with this years theme of the "Cargo Cult" we will discuss situations in which small populations of subjugated people have maintained their beliefs in the face of hegemonic reprogramming efforts. As such, we will discuss the role of the individual in changing the default world to reflect the best of what the Burn represents via various methods of culture jamming and activism.

(Nothing but) Flowers a Talking Heads song, and meme for this discussion can be heard immediately following this event @DC not Washington Talking Heads dance party!

description:
This offering will be a combination of lecture and dialogue on the topic of open (non-monogamous) relationship as a path of awakening. Open relationships, and/or polyamory, are becoming more widely known to the general public as an alternative to the default cultural model of monogamous relationships. One of the first questions that comes up for someone when they first hear about open relationship is "Why?" Why would anyone choose this model of relationship? Certainly at the beginning of someone's exploration of open relationship (and often for sometime to come), it would seem a guaranteed way to bring up ones deepest fears and insecurities. So why do it? 

We will talk about open relationships and explore answers to these questions, from an unlikely frame, that of spiritual awakening. In my opinion, not only is open relationship compatible with a deep path of spiritual awakening, it may be one of the most profound ways to catalyze and walk that path.
print_description: This workshop will explore how Freedom (open relationships), and Love (the deepest commitment), can come together as a path of spiritual awakening.
title: Open Relationship as a Path of Awakening

description: What is your plastic footprint?  Take a walk through your house (or Burning Man camp) from plastic-packaged food in the kitchen to toothbrushes and shampoo in the bathroom, our world is full of plastic.  And at Burning Man, we are sleep in plastic sleeping bags in plastic tents and wear plastic goggles.  And how much of our food and water is packaged in plastic? Although some plastics make our lives better, much of it is a problem -- polluting our oceans and beaches and harming our health with toxic chemicals. But what can one person do to be part of the solution? Join us for inspiring stories and practical tips to reduce plastic in your home and on the Playa.  Author Beth Terry will share her journey from self-confessed plastic addict to empowered plastic-free activist and explain why we can't just recycle our way out of this mess.  You may even get to peek at her (nearly) plastic-free campsite.
print_description: Your plastic footprint? While plastics can make our lives better, much of is a problem, join us for inspiring stories and practical tip to reduce it!
title: Plastic-Free Burning Man Workshop

description:
Transforming Learning
August 30, 2013 
10AM – 4PM with a VERY HAPPY HOUR til 5

ASPIRE VILLAGE at the keyhole: Playaskool stage, IDEATE, SingularityU and Burning Man align for a one day gathering on playa to transform our learning landscape.

GO ON A TRANSFORMATIONAL ADVENTURE - CREATE WITH NERDS & GEEKS!
Interactive Summit for the playa learning communities

Learning technology enterprises, teachers, designers, developers and reformers....bring your brilliant ideas, questions and burning insights to share with your peers from around the world.

Chief nerds on the mic include Nolan Bushnell (founder of Atari, Chuck-E-Cheese and Brainrush), Brian Behlendorf (founder of Apache and former CTO of the World Economic Forum) and leading experts in education, creativity and technology. Open space unconference curated by Evonne Heyning with support from the Burning Man Project and ASPIRE Village. Bring your own research talks, games for learning and big ideas to alter the ways we inspire each other.

Participate in Actions:
 * Choose Your Transformational Adventure (cooperative discovery & play with others)
 * Write the Manifesto for Learning (collaborative vision for future)
 * Igniting Lightning Talks (short sharing sessions on research & development)
 * Unconference Afternoon Breakout Sessions (focused group workshops and interactive salons)
 * Lunch and interactive gifting with amazing leaders

Bring your research, your games and tech, anything you want to share with nerds and geeks from around the world!
print_description:
Burning Nerds Transformational Learning Day 
10am – 5pm
Speakers & research talks, adventures, gifts, lunch, breakout sessions, circles & happy hour
title: Playaskool & ASPIRE Village

description: Where have you been?  What have you seen? What did it mean? In the tradition of Terrence McKenna, we will get together and share our past voyages and impressions of the psychedelic experience. In the psychedelic state, to quote McKenna, "One hears and beholds a language of alien meaning that is conveying alien information that cannot be Englished. Being monkeys, when we encounter a translinguistic object, a kind of cognitive dissonance is set up in our hindbrain. We try to pour language over it and it sheds it like water off a duck's back." We will push the envelope of language to see if we can go ahead and English some of that alien information after all. Perhaps art, music or dance will play a part in expressing these otherwise inexpressible concepts. All are welcome, whether experienced with the psychedelic state or not. Please note: this is a discussion group only; illegal substances and activities are not welcome in our camp. Please respect our need to keep our camp safe and 100% legal. Thank you so much.
print_description:
Share your impressions of the psychedelic experience. Note: discussion group only; no illegal substances/activities. We  
keep our camp safe & legal.
title: Psychedelic Discussions

description:
Learn how trauma can be treated effectively in one session of less than 1-1/2 hours. This is an introduction to the amazingly effective, simple and ground-breaking work of Jon Connelly in restoring victims of severe trauma, including sexual violence and war veterans, to full function. (See rapidtrauma.com for more information).

 

The morning workshop will outline the content of an average session, and explain the principles at work that allow for rapid resolution. Attendees will benefit personally by tapping into the human mind’s power to heal and restore proper function after trauma – which is defined as anything stored in the human mind in a dysfunctional way.

 

The afternoon session will ask for volunteers to do a session, free of charge, with an audience observing. Life-changing, all will gain insights that will benefit them in their life and lead to a brighter, lighter, more peaceful and exciting life.

 

Class is taught by David Monroe, who has been a “scout” of healing technologies for years, and is certified in Rapid Trauma Resolution training.
print_description: Learn how trauma can be treated effectively in one session of less than 1-1/2 hours.
title: Rapid Trauma Resolution

description: My mind used to constantly be living in the future.  As a perfectionist that saw problems everywhere, I would dream about what would make me happy in the future or solve my problems, but it never came by living in the future.  Learn how your mind want to escape this moment by dreaming about the future or reliving the past, but true happiness is in the now (current moment).  Through connection with my higher self and new actions and seeing that there are no mistakes, I was able to stop escaping to the future and live in the now and find joy. Class will include instructor’s story and lessons learned followed by group sharing and then a 20 minute meditation to experience the now.
print_description: How to live in the moment by letting go of perfectionism and perceived mistakes so you can find the life you were born to live w/ Group Participation.

description: Join us in our Lotus Dome for the daily recitation of Nam Myoho Renge Kyo and morning gongyo (the practice of chanting two chapters from the Lotus Sutra) In the Lotus Sutra Shakymuni Buddha revealed that every human being can attain enlightment in their present form. Through chanting Nam Myoho Renge Kyo an individual is able to awaken this enlightenment the Buddha revealed and reveal their own buddha nature. A practitioner of this buddhism through chanting and study can transform their life and create a state of unshakable happiness overcoming the sufferings of birth and death. Buddhism is a practice and everyone is welcome to join. Each day after chanting together we will study a buddhist concept, answer questions and share experiences about the practice and its application to our daily life. All are welcome to join us even if you have never chanted before.
print_description: Chanting of Nam Myoho Renge Kyo & Lotus Sutra chapters. Join us to learn about practicing Buddhism and reveal your enlightened nature. All welcomed.
title: Recitation of Lotus Sutra: Nam Myoho Renge Kyo

description: As we find our path along that clock we call a road,Let the winds blow you towards 2 o'clk & K,There you will find a Village,An Intergalactic Sasquatch Village,~ In this Village will stand ~ The Rootist Temple ~Where a gift you shall receive,A gift for the body, A gift for mind,It is the hope of of the teacher,that each of you share what he is offering,that we can all re-connect in this way,~ bringing you back home to your center~~ Re-connection Yoga on the Playa ~ @ The Rootist Temple ~Offered Monday thru ThursdayEveryone morning at 11amIntergalactic Sasquatch Village @ The Rootist Temple 2&k,Have you been wondering what the Rootist Temple Stands for? Have you been wondering what is Rootism? Have you been wondering what is Rootist & PHY yoga? Well then, wonder no more:The Rootist understands that the path of oneness forks many roads. There are infinite possibilities from which we may choose along the way. It’s the journey.We will learn from our experiences as we evolve as humans, and we may hopefully learn to peel away the layers of illusion fostered by maturity and our life experiences. Through study and inquiry we may also find common threads from the ancient teachings linked to modern expressions of spirituality.We may even sense unity at some point.What is beautiful about life is that there are multiple unique levels of exploration within each of us. Each layer can reveal a different angle or new areas of focus for growth evolving us to become prismatic.Our potential is driven from the main spirit channel, the heart – the keeper of our spark. Our breathing, the spiritus from which the word spirit evolved, is feeding the spark.Self-Awareness happens when we identify and tap into the roots of our beliefs with evaluation and reflection.Rootism is the belief that the truth is all around us always yet often hidden like a gem in the rough waiting for us to discover it with great enthusiasm.

description: Black Rock City is a "Pack It In, Pack It Out" city, There are no trash cans or recycling bins. You are responsible for disposing of waste properly. Do you want to reduce the amount of recycling you will have to pack out? Start by separating your your recyclables from any landfill trash. Then separate all your aluminum cans and bring them to Black Rock City Recycle Camp. We are located in Center Camp at 6:00, directly behind the Cafe. The camp is "Open" and ready to accept your cans Monday through Sunday, 9am to 5pm. Bring your clean, separated aluminum cans only. We definitely don't want your trash. We also do not accept any other recyclables, you can take them to one of the 24 hour recycling stations on your way back to Reno, check out your Survival Guide for more information. We provide a sorting area to check your cans for anything that isn't aluminum. Then you can ride the bike powered can crusher and crush your cans. After your cans get crushed, you will put your crushed cans into the large containers at the camp. All proceeds from the aluminum are donated to the Gerlach K-12 School in Gerlach, NV. Come join in the fun while doing a good thing for the planet and Black Rock City..!
print_description: Want to reduce the amount of recycling you have to pack out? Awesome..! Separate your aluminum cans and bring them to Black Rock City Recycle Camp!!!
title: Recycle Your Aluminum Cans!!!

description: Finding ways to remain balanced and effective in your relationships (especially within the context of non-monogamy) can be daunting, as frequent interactions can be rife with assumptions, misnomers, and "but I thought we said's". What if there was a way to mitigate the unforeseen moments that occur? Perhaps your understandings could be bolstered with a Relationship Agreement? In this workshop we'll share with you what lessons we've learned in drafting, revising, and adhering to our relationship agreement over the years. We'll also engage you in how some of these ideas might be applicable for you and your partner(s). Nobody said communication and intention in relationships was easy; we're looking to help add some texture and solidity to your foundation.
print_description: Communication and intention in relationships isn't easy! We'll show you effective ways to keep balance, solidity, and texture in your relationship.

description:
Looking for a play partner?
Join the ribbon party at Retrofrolic ALL WEEK LONG!
The ribbons are an invitation to flirt, negotiate and play with each other. They show that you are seeking a play partner tonight and what kind of play you are interested in.
Wearing ribbons gives permission for others to approach you with play invitations and lets you see at a glance who might be interested in being approached by you.

If you are a DOMINANT/top, wear your ribbons on your LEFT wrist.

If you are a SUBMISSIVE/bottom, wear your ribbons on the RIGHT.

Switch? Slutty? Wear them on BOTH sides!

No one is obligated, consider this a color coded ice breaker.
This ribbon code is loosely based on the famous "hanky code", but we have made some changes (to make it easier).
print_description:

description: Most of how we experience the world is relative to the things around us - our frame of reference.  With "Ride the Wind" you lay back on an air mattress so that all you see is this VERY LARGE white fabric floating horizontally on the wind.  After a couple of minutes your mind with adopt the fabric as it's frame of reference and your body will gain the sensation of floating relative to the fabric.  Now explore the patterns the wind creates, and feel them flow through you.

description:
Jamaican band Rootz Underground comes to Burning Man and Reverbia, along with Southern Oregon favorites Indubious...for a night of Reggae, I-Vibes, and Dance Riddims.  This will be the first major Jamaican band to ever perform in Black Rock City...and Burners will not want to miss out on this once in a decade show.  Rootz Underground is a large festival act who tours throughout the World and is well known in Europe and in the US.  www.rootzunderground.com   

Conscious Reggae Hip Hop Artist Wisdom with musician drummer Tomkat McCree, and DJ Solrising will also be performing at 9:30pm.  Wisdom hosted 2013 Reggae on the River and has been performing on Main Stages at festivals across the West Coast.
DJ Solrising is the former US Scratching Champion.

Also performing at 8:45pm, Buckman Coe will be performing a new solo looping set.  Buckman's band was voted 2013 Best Band in Vancouver, BC.  and Buckman has also played at many festivals across Canada and the West Coast US. 

Opening the night will be Shovelman.  The well known sound looper who plays a shovel that is stringed like a guitar.  Shovelman is a favorite on the US festival circuit and will set the tone for this great evening of talent at Reverbia's Urban Night Concerts.
print_description: Jamaican band Rootz Underground comes to Burning Man for the first time, joined by Indubious...for an amazing night of Reggae, I-Vibes, and Dancing.
title: Rootz Underground w/Wisdom, Buckman Coe

description: Come get your latin dance on! In this dance workshop we will learn beginner level Salsa Rueda. Upon completion dancers will be able to recognize about 10 move "calls" and dance them confidently and joyously. Salsa Rueda (aka "Casino de Rueda") is a particular type of circle dancing to Salsa music. It was developed in Havana, Cuba in the late 1950s and early 1960s by the group Guaracheros de Regla. Pairs of dancers form a circle, with dance moves called out by one person, a caller. Many moves involve the swapping of partners creating a fun, synchronized, playful community circle dance.
print_description: Come get your latin dance on! In this workshop we will learn beginner level Cuban Salsa. Learn to groove with partners to the rhythmic tunes of Cuba!
title: Salsa Rueda Dance

description:
Ho ye!  Hey, Mukker!
You know who you are… maybe not Scottish by birth, but a single malt lover nonetheless.  Beautiful scotch, the more exotic and unique, the better.  If you understand – really understand – then this year at Burning Man, we may just have an event worth crossing the playa for.
Bring a bottle of your favorite drop to the Mystikal Misfits bar (4:30 & B) at 2 pm, Wednesday, August 28th.   Come armed with a strong thirst (if not an obsession) for rare single malts – the kind of bottlings that spark rave reviews and win awards.  Nothing blended, nothing commonplace.  Caress to impress with a spectacular scotch you’d like to turn the playa onto.  Once inside our exclusive event – NO BOTTLE, NO ENTRY – you will partake of Scottish music and nibbles with like-minded desert kiltsmen and women.
So while spewing feathers in the heat of the day, don’t be a numpty and end up blustered from just any bad swally and scran…  Settle into a little Misfit hospitality and savor the kind of “cargo” cults were actually started over…  You know at least one of the scotches will be spectacular, because you’re going to bring it.
And a dram good time will be had by all!

Entry requires a bottle of unique single malt scotch (no blends) , where you'll join other like-minded fans for a once-in-a-playa tasting they'll write bagpipe songs about.
print_description: Entry requires a bottle of unique single malt scotch, where you'll join other like-minded fans for a once-in-a-playa tasting they'll write songs about
title: Scotchfest 2013

description:
Meet your death ritual. Surrender to the inevitable but now. Release ego, social ties, stuckness.  Come back more alive than ever. Shaman initiation.
Release old stories around your personna and ego bruises.
Surrender to the inevitable but now.  die. die and come back more alive than you have been in ever so long.
we finish you off.  this could work in your favor.
 On Mon, Jun 3, 2013 at 10:38 PM, Mackenzie Elizabeth Amara ‪<mea309@nyu.edu>‬ wrote:‬
SCENARIO: AS RITUAL, WE DON’T PRE ANNOUNCE THIS.  participants enter the space and are immediately blindfolded and given earplugs to put in. we then gently lie them down in a circle, where they silently lay for a few minutes. at some point, someone begins to sprinkle dirt (earth) over them, to represent a burial. at some point, we gently have them rise (still blindfolded) and line them up, placing the hands of each person on the shoulders of the person in front of them. accompanied by drums, rattles, windchimes, flutes, etc. we walk them out to some chosen, semi-remote place on the playa. once there, we paint them with white paint (in ritual markings, not the whole body) and remove their blindfolds and ear plugs. we instruct them to embody various forms of development as we walk back to the original spot - first sliding over the earth, then crawling, then walking, and finally running. perhaps even dancing by the end. reaching our end, we break out into full celebration and incorporation, simultaneously mourning the person that has just died and celebrating the new person that has made the journey back with us.
print_description: Meet your death ritual. Surrender to the inevitable but now. Release ego, social ties, stuckness.  Come back more alive than ever. Shaman initiation.
title: Shaman's Death
